BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Food and Mood
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260413T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260413T200000
DTSTAMP:20260509T064410Z
UID:4e05ade8fd3c09e1@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a noontime webinar to discover how your daily diet
  impacts not just your physical health\, but also your brain function and 
 emotional resilience.\n\nYou will learn how the foods we eat influence our
  gut microbiome\, which communicates with our immune system and ultimately
  affects neurotransmitter signaling in our brains. We'll delve into the be
 nefits of the Mediterranean Diet for gut health and how to incorporate its
  mood-boosting principles into any lifestyle.\n\nWe'll also uncover how su
 gar and refined carbohydrates affect hormones and cortisol levels. You wil
 l learn practical strategies to manage the blood sugar effects of these fo
 ods\, enabling you to consume carbohydrates wisely for optimal health and 
 well-being.\n\nBy the end of the session\, you'll have a deeper understand
 ing of the science behind nutrition's impact on the brain and mood\, along
  with practical tips for enhancing your well-being through diet.\n\nThis c
 lass will be recorded and a one-week link to the recording will be shared 
 with all registered participants. To receive incentive points\, attend at 
 least 80% of the live session or listen to the entire recording within one
  week.  Request disability accommodations and access info.\n\nClass detail
 s are subject to change.\n\nEvent URL: https://events.stanford.edu/event/f
 ood-and-mood-7947\n\nSource: stanford_virtual
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/food-and-mood-7947
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: Food and Mood
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
