SUMMARY:Models\, Inference & Algorithms (MIA) Meeting
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260506T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260506T160000
DTSTAMP:20260509T064410Z
UID:3af3e312b0433733@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Talks
DESCRIPTION:Please join us on Wednesday\, May 6 for our MIA meeting featur
 ing Ohad Lewin-Epstein and Chris Smillie\, both from Harvard Medical Schoo
 l!\n\n \n\n📅 Wednesday\, May 6\n\n \n\n🎤 Primer\, 9:00 am\n\n💬 Ch
 ris Smillie\n\n🏫 Harvard Medical School\n\n \n\n🎤 Seminar\, 10:00 am
 : A global microbiome axis underlying susceptibility to immune-mediated di
 seases\n\n💬 Ohad Lewin-Epstein \n\n🏫 Harvard Medical School\n\n \n\n
 Hosted by the Eric and Wendy Schmidt Center\, the MIA Initiative (Models\,
  Inference & Algorithms) supports learning and collaboration across the in
 terface of biology and medicine with mathematics\, statistics\, machine le
 arning\, and computer science. We bring together scientists every Wednesda
 y in Acadia (Broad Institute – 75 Ames St.\, M1) and virtually. A primer
  starts at 9:00 am\, followed by a seminar and discussion at 10:00 am and 
 10:50 am\, respectively.\n\n \n\n💌 Email us to join our mailing list fo
 r Zoom links: mia-team@broadinstitute.org\n\n \n\n🧑‍🏫 Read the abs
 tracts and see the full schedule: broad.io/MIA \n\n📺 Watch previous tal
 ks: broad.io/MIAPlaylist \n\n🗓️ View our calendar: broad.io/mia-calen
 dar \n\n \n\n❓ Ask questions: mia-team@broadinstitute.org\n\n \n\n**If y
 ou do not have a Broad badge\, please arrive at the 75 Ames Street entranc
 e 10 minutes early with an ID to check in with security. We will escort fo
 lks up at 8:55 am and 9:55 am\; please email mia-team@broadinstitute.org i
 f you arrive outside of these times.\n\nEvent URL: https://events.broadins
 titute.org/event/models-inference-algorithms-mia-meeting-3282\n\nSource: b
 road_institute
LOCATION:Broad Institute\, Acadia (M1)
URL:https://events.broadinstitute.org/event/models-inference-algorithms-mi
 a-meeting-3282
